CEMACS Experiment Daily Report

Yusri Yusup, PhD

Air-sea flux exchanges and weather parameters

Date: 2017-06-10

This page shows the previous day half-hourly 24-hour measurements of carbon dioxide flux, latent and sensible heat fluxes and other weather parameters from the CEMACS eddy covariance station. Data is from 18:00 to 17:30.

Carbon dioxide flux (CO2 flux)

This plots shows the vertical movement or fluxes of carbon dioxide (CO2) from the water and land surfaces surrounding the station.

Latent heat (LE)

This plots shows the vertical movement of moisutre or latent heat (LE) from the water and land surfaces surrounding the station.

Sensible heat (H)

This plots shows the vertical movement or fluxes of dry heat or sensible heat (H) from the water and land surfaces surrounding the station.
